# For Build/Third-Party/ ships the tools Deploy.exe needs at runtime and is
# tracked in git as regular (in a couple of cases multi-MB) blobs - this repo
# is managed with jj, which as of writing doesn't support Git LFS or even
# .gitattributes at all (https://github.com/jj-vcs/jj/issues/80), so there's
# no way to avoid that. Tracking the larger files here needs
# `jj config set --repo snapshot.max-new-file-size "20MiB"` once per clone -
# jj's default 1MiB cap on new file snapshots will otherwise refuse them.
# Don't ignore the whole directory here - that would stop git from tracking
# the files that ARE meant to be committed too (gitignore doesn't look inside
# a directory it's already ignoring).
#
# For Build/Fetched Third-Party/, a sibling folder, is the opposite: tools
# that DO have a stable public release to pull from, so
# scripts/fetch-third-party.js downloads them there instead of duplicating
# them in git history. Fully ignored, unlike Third-Party/ above.
/For Build/Fetched Third-Party
tests/mods
